dosageInstruction.text:
15-30 g of dextrose, Oral, PRN, Low blood sugar, Starting on Mon 5/1/23 at 1205
If INITIAL blood glucose is between 50-69 mg/dL, give 15 grams (1 tube) of glucose gel orally and NOTIFY PROVIDER.  If INITIAL blood glucose is less than 50 mg/dL, give 30 grams (2 tubes) of glucose gel orally and NOTIFY PROVIDER.  If RECHECKED blood glucose is less than 70 mg/dL, repeat above treatment steps until blood glucose is greater than or equal to 70 mg/dL above and NOTIFY PROVIDER.
Until Fri 5/5/23 at 1808

1 mg, Intramuscular, PRN, Low blood sugar, Blood glucose less than 70 mg/dL and NOTIFY PROVIDER, Starting on Mon 5/1/23 at 1205
Reconstitute 1 mg vial with 1 mL of STERILE WATER FOR INJECTION for a concentration of 1 mg/mL. Withdraw ordered volume and transfer to a syringe for administration.  
Until Fri 5/5/23 at 1808

125-250 mL, Intravenous, PRN, Low blood sugar, Starting on Mon 5/1/23 at 1205
If INITIAL blood glucose is between 50-69 mg/dL, give 125 mL 10% dextrose intravenously over 8 minutes and NOTIFY PROVIDER.     If INITIAL blood glucose is less than 50 mg/dL, give 250 mL 10% dextrose intravenously over 15 minutes and NOTIFY PROVIDER.  If RECHECKED blood glucose is less than 70 mg/dL, give 250 mL 10% dextrose intravenously over 15 minutes and NOTIFY PROVIDER. If ordered rate exceeds 999 ml/hr an infusion pump is not required for administration and may infuse as fast as the patient's access will allow.
Until Fri 5/5/23 at 1808
